\c 25
\s1 The Plague of Israel
\m 
\v 1 When Israel dwelled in Shittim, the people began to prostitute\f + \fr 25:1 \ft Or “have sexual relations” \f* \add themselves\add* with the daughters of Moab. 
\v 2 And they invited the people to the sacrifices of their gods, and the people ate and worshiped their gods. 
\v 3 So Israel was joined together to Baal Peor, and ⸤Yahweh became angry⸥\f + \fr 25:3 \ft Literally “the nose of Yahweh became hot” \f* with Israel. 
\v 4 Yahweh said to Moses, “Take all ⸤the leaders⸥\f + \fr 25:4 \ft Literally “the heads” \f* of the people and kill them before the sun, so the fierce anger of Yahweh will turn from Israel.” 
\v 5 So Moses said to the judges of Israel, “Each \add of you\add* kill his men who are joined together with Baal Peor.”
\p 
\v 6 And behold, a man from the ⸤Israelites⸥\f + \fr 25:6 \ft Literally “sons/children of Israel” \f* came and brought to his brothers \add a\add* Midianite woman before the eyes of Moses and before the eyes of all of the community of the ⸤Israelites⸥,\f + \fr 25:6 \ft Literally “sons/children of Israel” \f* and they \add were\add* weeping \add at\add* the doorway of the tent of assembly. 
\v 7 When Phinehas son of Eleazar son of Aaron the priest saw, he got up from the midst of the community and took a spear in his hand. 
\v 8 He went after the man of Israel into the woman’s section of the tent, and he drove the two of them, the man of Israel and the woman, into her belly. And the plague among the ⸤Israelites⸥\f + \fr 25:8 \ft Literally “sons/children of Israel” \f* stopped. 
\v 9 The ones who died in the plague were twenty-four thousand.
\p 
\v 10 Yahweh spoke to Moses, saying, 
\v 11 “Phinehas son of Eleazar, son of Aaron the priest, turned away my anger from among the ⸤Israelites⸥\f + \fr 25:11 \ft Literally “sons/children of Israel” \f* when he was jealous with my jealousy in their midst, and I did not destroy the ⸤Israelites⸥\f + \fr 25:11 \ft Literally “sons/children of Israel” \f* with my jealousy. 
\v 12 Therefore say, ‘Behold, I \add am\add* giving to him my covenant of peace, 
\v 13 and it will be for him and his ⸤offspring⸥\f + \fr 25:13 \ft Literally “seed” \f* after him a covenant of an eternal priesthood because he was jealous for his God and made atonement for the ⸤Israelites⸥.’ ”\f + \fr 25:13 \ft Literally “sons/children of Israel” \f*
\p 
\v 14 The name of the man of Israel who was struck with the Midianite woman \add was\add* Zimri son of Salu, a leader of ⸤the family⸥\f + \fr 25:14 \ft Or “the father’s house” or “the ancestor’s house” \f* of the Simeonites.\f + \fr 25:14 \ft Hebrew “Simeonite” \f* 
\v 15 The name of the Midianite woman who was struck \add was\add* Cozbi daughter of Zur, ⸤a leader⸥\f + \fr 25:15 \ft Literally “a head” \f* of \add a\add* tribe of ⸤the family⸥\f + \fr 25:15 \ft Or “the father’s house” or “the ancestor’s house” \f* in Midian.
\p 
\v 16 Yahweh spoke to Moses, saying, 
\v 17 “Attack the Midianites and strike them 
\v 18 because they \add were\add* attacking you with their deception, \add with\add* which they have deceived you on the matter of Peor and on the matter of Cozbi the daughter of the leader of Midian, their sister who was struck on the day of the plague because of the matter of Peor.”
\c 26
\s1 A New Census
\m 
\v 1 \f + \fr 26:1 \ft \xt Numbers 26:1a \ft in the English Bible is 25:19b in the Hebrew Bible \f* And it happened after the plague, \f + \fr 26:1 \ft In the Hebrew Bible, \xt Numbers 26:1 \ft begins here \f*Yahweh said to Moses and to Eleazar son of Aaron the priest, saying, 
\v 2 “⸤Take a census⸥\f + \fr 26:2 \ft Literally “Lift up the head\fq s \ft ” \f* of the community of the ⸤Israelites⸥\f + \fr 26:2 \ft Literally “sons/children of Israel” \f* from ⸤those twenty years old⸥\f + \fr 26:2 \ft Literally “a son of twenty years” \f* and above, according to ⸤their families⸥,\f + \fr 26:2 \ft Literally “the house of their fathers” \f* all who are able to go out to war in Israel.” 
\v 3 So Moses and Eleazar the priest spoke with them on the desert-plateau of Moab by \add the\add* Jordan \add across from\add* Jericho, saying, 
\v 4 “\add Take a census of the community\add* from ⸤those twenty years old⸥\f + \fr 26:4 \ft Literally “a son of twenty years” \f* and above, just as Yahweh commanded Moses.”
\p The Israelites who went out from the land of Egypt \add were\add*:
\p 
\v 5 Reuben, the firstborn of Israel, the descendants\f + \fr 26:5 \ft Or “sons” \f* of Reuben: \add of\add* Hanoch, the clan of the Hanochites; of Pallu, the clan of the Palluites;\f + \fr 26:5 \ft Hebrew “Palluite” \f* 
\v 6 of Hezron, the clan of the Hezronites;\f + \fr 26:6 \ft Hebrew “Hezronite” \f* of Carmi, the clan of the Carmites.\f + \fr 26:6 \ft Hebrew “Carmite” \f* 
\v 7 These \add are\add* the clans of the Reubenites,\f + \fr 26:7 \ft Hebrew “Reubenite” \f* and the ones counted of them were forty-three thousand seven hundred and thirty. 
\v 8 The children of Pallu: Eliab. 
\v 9 The children of Eliab: Nemuel, Dathan, and Abiram. These \add are the same\add* Dathan and Abiram who \add were\add* appointed of the community, who rebelled against Moses and Aaron in the company of Korah, when they rebelled against Yahweh, 
\v 10 and the land opened its mouth and swallowed them with Korah, when that company died, when the fire consumed two hundred and fifty men, and they were a sign.\f + \fr 26:10 \ft That is, a warning sign \f* 
\v 11 The children\f + \fr 26:11 \ft Or “sons” \f* of Korah, however, did not die.
\p 
\v 12 The descendants\f + \fr 26:12 \ft Or “sons” \f* of Simeon, according to their clans: of Nemuel, the clan of the Nemuelites;\f + \fr 26:12 \ft Hebrew “Nemuelite” \f* of Jamin, the clan of the Jaminites;\f + \fr 26:12 \ft Hebrew “Jaminite” \f* of Jakin, the clan of the Jakinites;\f + \fr 26:12 \ft Hebrew “Jakinite” \f* 
\v 13 of Zerah, the clan of the Zerahites;\f + \fr 26:13 \ft Hebrew “Zerahite” \f* of Shaul, the clan of the Shaulites.\f + \fr 26:13 \ft Hebrew “Shaulite” \f* 
\v 14 These \add were\add* the clans of the Simeonites,\f + \fr 26:14 \ft Hebrew “Simeonite” \f* twenty-two thousand two hundred.
\p 
\v 15 The descendants\f + \fr 26:15 \ft Or “sons” \f* of Gad according to their clans: of Zephon, the clan of the Zephonites;\f + \fr 26:15 \ft Hebrew “Zephonite” \f* of Haggi, the clan of the Haggites;\f + \fr 26:15 \ft Hebrew “Haggite” \f* of Shuni, the clan of the Shunites;\f + \fr 26:15 \ft Hebrew “Shunite” \f* 
\v 16 of Ozni, the clan of the Oznites;\f + \fr 26:16 \ft Hebrew “Oznite” \f* of Eri, the clan of the Erites;\f + \fr 26:16 \ft Hebrew “Erite” \f* 
\v 17 of Arod, the clan of the Arodites;\f + \fr 26:17 \ft Hebrew “Arodite” \f* of Areli, the clan of the Arelites;\f + \fr 26:17 \ft Hebrew “Arelite” \f* 
\v 18 These \add were\add* the clans of the descendants\f + \fr 26:18 \ft Or “sons” \f* of Gad according to the ones counted of them, forty thousand five hundred.
\p 
\v 19 The sons of Judah: Er and Onan; but Er and Onan died in the land of Canaan. 
\v 20 The descendants\f + \fr 26:20 \ft Or “sons” \f* of Judah according to their clans \add were\add*: of Shelah, the clan of the Shelanites;\f + \fr 26:20 \ft Hebrew “Shelanite” \f* of Perez, the clan of the Perezites;\f + \fr 26:20 \ft Hebrew “Perezite” \f* of Zerah, the clan of the Zerahites.\f + \fr 26:20 \ft Hebrew “Zerahite” \f* 
\v 21 The children of Perez were: of Hezron, the clan of the Hezronites;\f + \fr 26:21 \ft Hebrew “Hezronite” \f* of Hamul, the clan of the Hamulites.\f + \fr 26:21 \ft Hebrew “Hamulite” \f* 
\v 22 These \add were\add* the clans of Judah according to the ones counted of them, seventy-six thousand five hundred.
\p 
\v 23 The descendants\f + \fr 26:23 \ft Or “sons” \f* of Issachar according to their clans: \add of\add* Tola, the clan of the Tolaites;\f + \fr 26:23 \ft Hebrew “Tolaite” \f* of Puvah, the clan of the Punites;\f + \fr 26:23 \ft Hebrew “Punite” \f* 
\v 24 of Jashub, the clans of the Jashubites;\f + \fr 26:24 \ft Hebrew “Jashubite” \f* of Shimron, the clan of the Shimronites.\f + \fr 26:24 \ft Hebrew “Shimronite” \f* 
\v 25 These \add were\add* the clans of Issachar according to the ones counted of them, sixty-four thousand three hundred.
\p 
\v 26 The descendants\f + \fr 26:26 \ft Or “sons” \f* of Zebulun according to their clans: of Sered, the clan of the Seredites;\f + \fr 26:26 \ft Hebrew “Seredite” \f* of Elon, the clan of the Elonites;\f + \fr 26:26 \ft Hebrew “Elonite” \f* of Jahleel, the clan of the Jahleelites.\f + \fr 26:26 \ft Hebrew “Jahleelite” \f* 
\v 27 These \add were\add* the clans of the Zebulunites\f + \fr 26:27 \ft Hebrew “Zebulunite” \f* according to the ones counted of them, sixty thousand five hundred.
\p 
\v 28 The descendants\f + \fr 26:28 \ft Or “sons” \f* of Joseph according to their clans: Manasseh and Ephraim. 
\v 29 The descendants\f + \fr 26:29 \ft Or “sons” \f* of Manasseh: of Makir, the clan of the Makirites.\f + \fr 26:29 \ft Hebrew “Makirite” \f* And Makir fathered Gilead; of Gilead, the clan of the Gileadites.\f + \fr 26:29 \ft Hebrew “Gileadite” \f* 
\v 30 These \add were\add* the descendants\f + \fr 26:30 \ft Or “sons” \f* of Gilead: \add of\add* Iezer, the clan of the Iezerites;\f + \fr 26:30 \ft Hebrew “Iezerite” \f* of Helek, the clan of the Helekites;\f + \fr 26:30 \ft Hebrew “Helekite” \f* 
\v 31 and \add of\add* Asriel, the clan of the Asrielites;\f + \fr 26:31 \ft Hebrew “Asrielite” \f* and \add of\add* Shechem, the clan of the Shechemites;\f + \fr 26:31 \ft Hebrew “Shechemite” \f* 
\v 32 and \add of\add* Shemida, the clan of the Shemidaites;\f + \fr 26:32 \ft Hebrew “Shemidaite” \f* and \add of\add* Hepher, the clan of the Hepherites.\f + \fr 26:32 \ft Hebrew “Hepherite” \f* 
\v 33 Zelophehad son of Hepher did not have sons, but only daughters; and the names\f + \fr 26:33 \ft Hebrew “name” \f* of the daughters of Zelophehad \add were\add* Mahlah, Noah, Hoglah, Milcah, and Tirzah. 
\v 34 These \add were\add* the clans of Manasseh, and the ones counted of them \add were\add* fifty-two thousand seven hundred.
\p 
\v 35 These \add were\add* the descendants\f + \fr 26:35 \ft Or “sons” \f* of Ephraim according to their clans: of Shuthelah, the clan of the Shuthelahites;\f + \fr 26:35 \ft Hebrew “Shuthelahite” \f* of Beker, the clan of the Bekerites;\f + \fr 26:35 \ft Hebrew “Bekerite” \f* of Tahan, the clan of the Tahanites.\f + \fr 26:35 \ft Hebrew “Tahanite” \f* 
\v 36 And these \add were\add* the descendants\f + \fr 26:36 \ft Or “sons” \f* of Shuthelah: of Eran, the family of the Eranites.\f + \fr 26:36 \ft Hebrew “Eranite” \f* 
\v 37 These \add were\add* the clans of the descendants\f + \fr 26:37 \ft Or “sons” \f* of Ephraim according to the ones counted of them, thirty-two thousand five hundred. These \add were\add* the descendants\f + \fr 26:37 \ft Or “sons” \f* of Joseph according to their clans.
\p 
\v 38 The descendants\f + \fr 26:38 \ft Or “sons” \f* of Benjamin according to their clans: of Bela, the clan of the Belaites;\f + \fr 26:38 \ft Hebrew “Belaite” \f* of Ashbel, the clan of the Ashbelites;\f + \fr 26:38 \ft Hebrew “Ashbelite” \f* of Ahiram, the clan of the Ahiramites;\f + \fr 26:38 \ft Hebrew “Ahiramite” \f* 
\v 39 of Shephupham, the clan of the Shuphamites;\f + \fr 26:39 \ft Hebrew “Shuphamite” \f* of Hupham, the clan of the Huphamites.\f + \fr 26:39 \ft Hebrew “Huphamite” \f* 
\v 40 The sons of Bela were Ard and Naaman: \add of Ard\add*, the clan of the Ardites;\f + \fr 26:40 \ft Hebrew “Ardite” \f* of Naaman, the clan of the Naamites.\f + \fr 26:40 \ft Hebrew “Naamite” \f* 
\v 41 These \add were\add* the descendants\f + \fr 26:41 \ft Or “sons” \f* of Benjamin according to their clans. And the ones counted of them \add were\add* forty-five thousand six hundred.
\p 
\v 42 These \add were\add* the descendants\f + \fr 26:42 \ft Or “sons” \f* of Dan according to their clans: of Shuham, the clan of the Shuhamites.\f + \fr 26:42 \ft Hebrew “Shuhamite” \f* These \add were\add* the clans of Dan according to their clans. 
\v 43 All the clans of the Shuhamites,\f + \fr 26:43 \ft Hebrew “Shumhamite” \f* according to the ones counted of them, \add were\add* sixty-four thousand four hundred.
\p 
\v 44 The descendants\f + \fr 26:44 \ft Or “sons” \f* of Asher according to their clans: of Imnah, the clan of the Imnahites;\f + \fr 26:44 \ft Hebrew “Imnahite” \f* of Ishvi, the clan of the Ishvites;\f + \fr 26:44 \ft Hebrew “Ishvite” \f* of Beriah, the clan of the Beriahites.\f + \fr 26:44 \ft Hebrew “Beriahite” \f* 
\v 45 The descendants\f + \fr 26:45 \ft Or “sons” \f* of Beriah: of Heber, the clan of the Heberites;\f + \fr 26:45 \ft Hebrew “Heberite” \f* of Malkiel, the clan of the Malkielites.\f + \fr 26:45 \ft Hebrew “Malkielite” \f* 
\v 46 The name of the daughter of Asher \add was\add* Serah. 
\v 47 These \add were\add* the clans of the descendants\f + \fr 26:47 \ft Or “sons” \f* of Asher according to the ones counted of them, fifty-three thousand four hundred.
\p 
\v 48 The descendants\f + \fr 26:48 \ft Or “sons” \f* of Naphtali according to their clans: of Jahzeel, the clan of the Jahzeelites;\f + \fr 26:48 \ft Hebrew “Jahzeelite” \f* of Guni, the clan of the Gunites;\f + \fr 26:48 \ft Hebrew “Gunite” \f* 
\v 49 of Jezer, the clan of the Jezerites;\f + \fr 26:49 \ft Hebrew “Jezerite” \f* of Shillem, the clan of the Shillemites.\f + \fr 26:49 \ft Hebrew “Shillemite” \f* 
\v 50 These \add were\add* the clans of Naphtali according to their clans, the ones counted of them, forty-five thousand four hundred.
\p 
\v 51 These \add were\add* the ones counted of the ⸤Israelites⸥,\f + \fr 26:51 \ft Literally “sons/children of Israel” \f* six hundred and one thousand seven hundred and thirty.
\p 
\v 52 Then Yahweh spoke to Moses, saying, 
\v 53 “For these the land must be divided as an inheritance according to the number of names. 
\v 54 For the larger group you must increase their inheritance, and for the smaller group you must make smaller their inheritance; each must be given ⸤their⸥\f + \fr 26:54 \ft Hebrew “his” \f* inheritance according to the number of the ones counted of them. 
\v 55 Surely the land will be divided by lot. They will inherit according to the names of the tribes of their ancestors.\f + \fr 26:55 \ft Or “fathers” \f* 
\v 56 ⸤Their⸥\f + \fr 26:56 \ft Hebrew “His” \f* inheritance must be divided according to the lot between the larger and smaller \add groups\add*.”
\p 
\v 57 These \add are\add* the ones counted of the Levites according to their clans: of Gershon, the clan of the Gershonites;\f + \fr 26:57 \ft Hebrew “Gershonite” \f* of Kohath, the clan of the Kohathites;\f + \fr 26:57 \ft Hebrew “Kohathite” \f* of Merari, the clan of the Merarites.\f + \fr 26:57 \ft Hebrew “Merarite” \f* 
\v 58 These \add are\add* the clans of Levi: the clan of the Libnites,\f + \fr 26:58 \ft Hebrew “Libnite” \f* the clan of the Hebronites,\f + \fr 26:58 \ft Hebrew “Hebronite” \f* the clan of the Mahlites,\f + \fr 26:58 \ft Hebrew “Mahlite” \f* the clan of the Mushites,\f + \fr 26:58 \ft Hebrew “Mushite” \f* the clan of the Korahites.\f + \fr 26:58 \ft Hebrew “Korahite” \f* Kohath fathered Amram. 
\v 59 The name of the wife of Amram \add was\add* Jochebed, the daughter of Levi, whose \add mother\add* bore her for Levi in Egypt; she bore to Amram: Aaron and Moses and their sister Miriam. 
\v 60 To Aaron were born Nadab and Abihu, Eleazar and Ithamar. 
\v 61 But Nadab and Abihu died when they presented strange fire ⸤before⸥\f + \fr 26:61 \ft Literally “in the presence of” \f* Yahweh. 
\v 62 The ones counted were twenty-three thousand, every male from ⸤a month old⸥\f + \fr 26:62 \ft Literally “a son of one month” \f* and above, because they were not counted in the midst of the ⸤Israelites⸥\f + \fr 26:62 \ft Literally “sons/children of Israel” \f* since no inheritance was given to them in the midst of the ⸤Israelites⸥.\f + \fr 26:62 \ft Literally “sons/children of Israel” \f*
\p 
\v 63 These \add were\add* the ones counted by Moses and Eleazar the priest, who counted the ⸤Israelites⸥\f + \fr 26:63 \ft Literally “sons/children of Israel” \f* on the desert-plateau of Moab on \add the\add* Jordan \add across\add* Jericho. 
\v 64 And among these there was not a man of those counted by Moses and Aaron the priest, who counted the ⸤Israelites⸥\f + \fr 26:64 \ft Literally “sons/children of Israel” \f* in the desert of Sinai. 
\v 65 For Yahweh said to them, “They will surely die in the desert.” And not a man was left over from them, except Caleb son of Jephunneh and Joshua son of Nun.
\c 27
\s1 Laws of Inheritance
\m 
\v 1 Then the daughters of Zelophehad, the son of Hepher, the son of Gilead, the son of Makir, the son of Manasseh, of the clan of Manasseh the son of Joseph, came near; and these \add were\add* the names of his daughters: Mahlah, Noah, Hoglah, and Tirzah. 
\v 2 They stood before Moses and before Eleazar the priest and before the leaders of the entire community \add at\add* the doorway of the tent of assembly,\f + \fr 27:2 \ft Or “meeting” \f* saying, 
\v 3 “Our father died in the desert; he was not in the midst of the company of those who banded together against Yahweh in the company of Korah, but he died in his own sin, and he had no sons. 
\v 4 Why should the name of our father disappear from the midst of his clan because he does not have a son? Give us property in the midst of the brothers of our father.” 
\v 5 So Moses brought their case before Yahweh. 
\v 6 And Yahweh said to Moses, saying, 
\v 7 “⸤The statements of the daughters of Zelophehad are right⸥.\f + \fr 27:7 \ft Literally “Such as the daughters of Zelophehad \fq are \ft speaking” \f* You must surely give them \add the\add* property of an inheritance in the midst of their father’s brothers, and you must transfer the inheritance of their father to them. 
\v 8 And you must speak to the ⸤Israelites⸥,\f + \fr 27:8 \ft Literally “sons/children of Israel” \f* saying, ‘If a man dies and has no son, you must transfer his inheritance to his daughter. 
\v 9 And if he has no daughter, you must give his inheritance to his brothers. 
\v 10 If he has no brothers, then you must give his inheritance to his father’s brothers. 
\v 11 If his father has no brothers, then you must give his inheritance to his nearest relative from his own clan, and he will take possession of it. It will be as a decree of stipulation for the ⸤Israelites⸥,\f + \fr 27:11 \ft Literally “sons/children of Israel” \f* just as Yahweh commanded Moses.’ ”
\p 
\v 12 Yahweh said to Moses, “Go up to this mountain of Abarim, and see the land that I have given to the ⸤Israelites⸥.\f + \fr 27:12 \ft Literally “sons/children of Israel” \f* 
\v 13 When you see it, you will be gathered to your people, just as Aaron your brother was gathered, 
\v 14 because you rebelled against my word in the desert of Zin when the community quarreled regarding my holiness at the waters.” (These \add are\add* the waters of Meribah-Kadesh \add in\add* the desert of Zin.)
\s1 Joshua Succeeds Moses
\m 
\v 15 Yahweh spoke to Moses, saying, 
\v 16 “Let Yahweh, the God of the spirits of all flesh, appoint a man over the community 
\v 17 who will go out before them and will come in before them, and who will lead them out and bring them in, so the community of Yahweh will not be like a flock that does not have a shepherd.” 
\v 18 Then Yahweh said to Moses, “Take Joshua son of Nun, a man in whom is \add the\add* spirit, and place your hand on him. 
\v 19 Have him stand before Eleazar the priest and before the entire community, and ⸤commission him⸥\f + \fr 27:19 \ft Literally “command him” \f* ⸤in their sight⸥.\f + \fr 27:19 \ft Literally “before their eyes” \f* 
\v 20 You will give to him from your authority so that the entire community of Israel will ⸤obey him⸥.\f + \fr 27:20 \ft Literally “hear \fq him \ft ” \f* 
\v 21 He will stand before Eleazar the priest, who will ask for him by the decision\f + \fr 27:21 \ft Or “judgment” \f* of the Urim before Yahweh. On ⸤his command⸥\f + \fr 27:21 \ft Literally “his word” \f* they will go out, and at ⸤his command⸥\f + \fr 27:21 \ft Literally “his word” \f* they will come in, \add both\add* he and all of the ⸤Israelites⸥\f + \fr 27:21 \ft Literally “sons/children of Israel” \f* with him, the entire community.” 
\v 22 Moses did just as Yahweh commanded him, and he took Joshua and set him before Eleazar the priest and before the entire community. 
\v 23 And he placed his hands on him and ⸤commissioned him⸥\f + \fr 27:23 \ft Literally “commanded him” \f* just as Yahweh spoke by the hand of Moses.\f + \fr 27:23 \ft Or “through Moses” \f*
\c 28
\s1 Daily Sacrifice
\m 
\v 1 Yahweh spoke to Moses, saying, 
\v 2 “Command the ⸤Israelites⸥\f + \fr 28:2 \ft Literally “sons/children of Israel” \f* and say to them, ‘⸤You will be careful to present⸥\f + \fr 28:2 \ft Literally “you will observe to present” \f* my offering, my food of my offerings made by fire, of a fragrance of appeasement to me, at its appointed time.’ 
\v 3 You will say to them, ‘This \add is\add* the offering made by fire that you will offer to Yahweh: two male lambs without defect ⸤in their first year⸥\f + \fr 28:3 \ft Literally “sons of a year” \f* as a continual burnt offering each day. 
\v 4 You will offer one male lamb in the morning, and the second male lamb you will offer ⸤at twilight⸥,\f + \fr 28:4 \ft Literally “between the two evenings” \f* 
\v 5 and a tenth of an ephah of finely milled flour as a grain offering, mixed with a fourth of a measure of beaten oil. 
\v 6 It is a continual burnt offering that was ⸤ordained⸥\f + \fr 28:6 \ft Literally “done” \f* on Mount Sinai as a fragrance of appeasement, an offering made by fire for Yahweh. 
\v 7 The libation with it \add will be\add* a fourth of a liquid measure for each male lamb; in the sanctuary you will pour out the libation of fermented drink for Yahweh. 
\v 8 And the second male lamb you will offer ⸤at twilight⸥;\f + \fr 28:8 \ft Literally “between the two evenings” \f* as the grain offering of the morning and as its libation you will offer it, an offering made by fire, a fragrance of appeasement for Yahweh.
\p 
\v 9 “ ‘On the day of the Sabbath, two male lambs without defect ⸤in their first year⸥,\f + \fr 28:9 \ft Literally “sons of a year” \f* and two-tenths of finely milled flour mixed with oil \add for\add* a grain offering and its libation. 
\v 10 \add This is\add* the burnt offering every Sabbath \add in addition to\add* the continual burnt offering and its libation.
\p 
\v 11 “ ‘And at the beginning of each of your months, you will present a burnt offering for Yahweh: two bulls and one ram, seven male lambs without defect ⸤in their first year⸥;\f + \fr 28:11 \ft Literally “sons of a year” \f* 
\v 12 and three-tenths of finely milled flour mixed with oil \add for\add* a grain offering, for each bull; and two-tenths of finely milled flour mixed with oil \add for\add* a grain offering for the one ram; 
\v 13 and a tenth of finely milled flour mixed with oil \add as\add* a grain offering for each male lamb, for a burnt offering of a fragrance of appeasement, an offering of fire for Yahweh. 
\v 14 Their libations will be half a liquid measure of wine for the bull and a third of a liquid measure of wine for the ram and a fourth of a liquid measure of wine for the male lamb; this \add is\add* the burnt offering for every month for the months of the year. 
\v 15 And one male goat as a sin offering for Yahweh; it will be offered in addition to the continual burnt offering and its libation.
\p 
\v 16 “ ‘On the fourteenth day of the first month \add is\add* the Passover for Yahweh. 
\v 17 On the fifteenth day of this month \add is\add* a religious feast, unleavened bread must be eaten for seven days. 
\v 18 On the first day \add there will be\add* a holy convocation; ⸤you will not do any regular work⸥.\f + \fr 28:18 \ft Literally “you will not do work of labor” \f* 
\v 19 You will present an offering by fire, a burnt offering for Yahweh: two bulls and one ram and seven male lambs ⸤in their first year⸥;\f + \fr 28:19 \ft Literally “sons of a year” \f* they will be for you without defect. 
\v 20 For their grain offering, you will offer finely milled flour mixed with oil: three-tenths for the bull and two-tenths for the ram. 
\v 21 You will offer a tenth for each of the seven male lambs; 
\v 22 and a goat for one sin offering to make atonement for you. 
\v 23 You will offer these besides the burnt offering of the morning, which \add is\add* for the continual burnt offering. 
\v 24 Like this you will offer daily, for seven days, \add the\add* food of the offering made by fire, a fragrance of appeasement for Yahweh; it will be offered in addition to the continual burnt offering and its libation. 
\v 25 On the seventh day you will have a holy convocation; ⸤you will not do any regular work⸥.\f + \fr 28:25 \ft Literally “you will not do work of labor” \f*
\s1 Offerings for the Festival of Weeks
\m 
\v 26 “ ‘And on the day of firstfruits, when you are presenting a new offering for Yahweh during your Festival of Weeks, you will have a holy convocation; ⸤you will not do any regular work⸥.\f + \fr 28:26 \ft Literally “you will not do work of labor” \f* 
\v 27 You will present a burnt offering for a fragrance of appeasement for Yahweh: two bulls, one ram, seven male lambs ⸤in their first year⸥;\f + \fr 28:27 \ft Literally “sons of a year” \f* 
\v 28 and their grain offering will be finely milled flour mixed with oil: three-tenths for each bull, two-tenths for one ram, 
\v 29 a tenth for each of the male lambs; 
\v 30 and one male goat to make atonement for you. 
\v 31 In addition to the continual burnt offering and its grain offering, you will offer \add them\add* without defect with their libation.
\c 29
\s1 Offers for the Seventh Month
\m 
\v 1 “ ‘On the seventh month, on the first day of the month, you will have a holy convocation; ⸤you will not do any regular work⸥.\f + \fr 29:1 \ft Literally “you will not do work of labor” \f* It will be a day for you of blowing trumpets. 
\v 2 You will offer a burnt offering as a fragrance of appeasement for Yahweh: one bull, one ram, \add and\add* seven male lambs ⸤in their first year⸥;\f + \fr 29:2 \ft Literally “sons of a year” \f* they will be without defect. 
\v 3 Their grain offering will be finely milled flour mixed with oil: three-tenths for the bull, two-tenths for the ram; 
\v 4 and one-tenth for each of the seven male lambs; 
\v 5 with one male goat for a sin offering, to make atonement for you, 
\v 6 in addition to the burnt offering of the new moon and its grain offering, the continual burnt offering and its grain offering, and their libations, according to their stipulations, as a fragrance of appeasement by fire for Yahweh.
\s1 Offerings for the Day of Atonement
\m 
\v 7 “ ‘And on the tenth of this seventh month you will have a holy convocation, and ⸤you will afflict yourselves⸥;\f + \fr 29:7 \ft Literally “you will afflict your lives” or “you will afflict your souls” \f* you will not do any work. 
\v 8 You will present a burnt offering for Yahweh, a fragrance of appeasement: one bull, one ram, seven male lambs ⸤in their first year⸥;\f + \fr 29:8 \ft Literally “sons of a year” \f* they will be without defect. 
\v 9 And their grain offering \add will be of\add* finely milled flour mixed with oil: three-tenths for the bull, two-tenths for the one ram, 
\v 10 one-tenth for each of the seven male lambs; 
\v 11 one male goat for a sin offering, in addition to the sin offering of atonement and the continual burnt offering and its grain offering, and their libations.
\p 
\v 12 “ ‘Then on the fifteenth day of the seventh month you will have a holy convocation; ⸤you will not do any regular work⸥,\f + \fr 29:12 \ft Literally “you will not do work of labor” \f* and you will hold a religious feast for Yahweh for seven days. 
\v 13 You will present a burnt offering, an offering made by fire as a fragrance of appeasement for Yahweh: thirteen bulls, two rams, fourteen male lambs ⸤in their first year⸥;\f + \fr 29:13 \ft Literally “sons of a year” \f* they will be without defect. 
\v 14 And their grain offering \add will be of\add* finely milled flour mixed with oil: three-tenths for the bull, two-tenths for the one ram, 
\v 15 one-tenth for each of the seven male lambs; 
\v 16 and one male goat for a sin offering, in addition to the continual burnt offering, its grain offering, and its libation.
\p 
\v 17 “ ‘On the second day: twelve bulls, two rams, fourteen male lambs ⸤in their first year⸥;\f + \fr 29:17 \ft Literally “sons of a year” \f* they will be without defect; 
\v 18 and their grain offering and their libations for the bulls, for the rams, and for the male lambs, by their number according to the stipulation; 
\v 19 and one male goat for a sin offering, in addition to the continual burnt offering and its grain offering, and their libations.
\p 
\v 20 “ ‘On the third day: eleven bulls, two rams, fourteen male lambs without defect ⸤in their first year⸥;\f + \fr 29:20 \ft Literally “sons of a year” \f* 
\v 21 and their grain offering and their libations for the bulls, for the rams, and for the male lambs, by their number according to the stipulation; 
\v 22 and one male goat for a sin offering, in addition to the continual burnt offering, its grain offering, and its libation.
\p 
\v 23 “ ‘On the fourth day: ten bulls, two rams, fourteen male lambs without defect ⸤in their first year⸥;\f + \fr 29:23 \ft Literally “sons of a year” \f* 
\v 24 and their grain offering and their libations for the bulls, for the rams, and for the male lambs by their number according to the stipulation; 
\v 25 and one male goat for a sin offering, in addition to the continual burnt offering, its grain offering, and its libation.
\p 
\v 26 “ ‘On the fifth day: nine bulls, two rams, fourteen male lambs without defect ⸤in their first year⸥;\f + \fr 29:26 \ft Literally “sons of a year” \f* 
\v 27 and their grain offering and their libations for the bulls, for the rams, and for the male lambs by their number according to the stipulation; 
\v 28 and one male goat for a sin offering, in addition to the continual burnt offering, its grain offering, and its libation.
\p 
\v 29 “ ‘On the sixth day: eight bulls, two rams, fourteen male lambs without defect ⸤in their first year⸥;\f + \fr 29:29 \ft Literally “sons of a year” \f* and their grain offering and their libations for the bulls, for the rams, and for the male lambs by their number according to the stipulation; 
\v 30 and their grain offering and their libations for the bulls, for the rams, and for the male lambs by their number according to the stipulation; 
\v 31 and one male goat for a sin offering, in addition to the continual burnt offering, its grain offering, and its libation.
\p 
\v 32 “ ‘On the seventh day: seven bulls, two rams, fourteen male lambs without defect ⸤in their first year⸥;\f + \fr 29:32 \ft Literally “sons of a year” \f* 
\v 33 and their grain offering and their libations for the bulls, for the rams, and for the male lambs by their number according to the stipulation; 
\v 34 and one male goat for a sin offering, in addition to the continual burnt offering, its grain offering, and its libation.
\p 
\v 35 “ ‘On the eighth day you will have an assembly; ⸤you will not do any regular work⸥.\f + \fr 29:35 \ft Literally “you will not do work of labor” \f* 
\v 36 You will present a burnt offering, an offering made by fire as a fragrance of appeasement for Yahweh: one bull, one ram, seven male lambs without defect ⸤in their first year⸥;\f + \fr 29:36 \ft Literally “sons of a year” \f* 
\v 37 and their grain offering and their libations for the bulls, for the rams, and for the male lambs by their number according to the stipulation; 
\v 38 and one male goat for a sin offering, in addition to the continual burnt offering, its grain offering, and its libation.
\p 
\v 39 “ ‘You will present these to Yahweh at your appointed time, in addition to your vows and your freewill offerings, for your burnt offerings and for you grain offerings and for your libations and for your fellowship offerings.’ ”
\p 
\v 40 \f + \fr 29:40 \ft \xt Numbers 29:40–30:16 \ft in the English Bible is 30:1–17 in the English Bible \f* So Moses said to the ⸤Israelites⸥\f + \fr 29:40 \ft Literally “sons/children of Israel” \f* in accordance with all that Yahweh commanded Moses.
\c 30
\s1 Laws for Vows
\m 
\v 1 Then Moses spoke to ⸤the leaders⸥\f + \fr 30:1 \ft Literally “the heads” \f* of the tribes concerning the ⸤Israelites⸥,\f + \fr 30:1 \ft Literally “sons/children of Israel” \f* saying, “This \add is\add* the word that Yahweh commanded: 
\v 2 if a man makes a vow for Yahweh or swears an oath with a binding pledge on himself, he must not render his word invalid; he must do all that went out from his mouth.
\p 
\v 3 “If a woman makes a vow to Yahweh, and she binds a pledge \add on herself\add* in her father’s house in your childhood, 
\v 4 but if her father hears her vow or her pledge that she bound on herself and says nothing to her, then all her vows will stand, and every pledge that she binds on her life will stand. 
\v 5 If her father forbids her on the day he hears \add of it\add*, all her vows or her pledges that she bound on herself will not stand, and Yahweh will forgive her because her father has forgiven her.
\p 
\v 6 “If ⸤she has a husband⸥\f + \fr 30:6 \ft Literally “she is to a man” \f* while bound by her vows or a rash promise of her lips, 
\v 7 and her husband hears \add of it\add* and is silent on the day he hears \add it\add*, her vows will stand, and her pledge that she bound upon herself will stand. 
\v 8 But if on the day her husband hears \add of it\add*, he forbids her, then he will nullify her vow that she is under, and the rash promise of her lips that she bound on herself; and Yahweh will forgive her.
\p 
\v 9 “But the vow of a widow or a woman who is divorced, all that she binds on herself will stand on her. 
\v 10 But if she made a vow \add in\add* her husband’s house, or bound herself on a pledge with a sworn oath, 
\v 11 and her husband heard \add it\add* but was silent to her, and he did not forbid her, all her vows will stand and every pledge that she bound on herself will stand. 
\v 12 But if her husband nullified them on the day he hears \add them\add*, all her vows going out of her lips concerning her vows or the pledge on herself will not stand; her husband has nullified them, and Yahweh will forgive her.
\p 
\v 13 “Any vow and any sworn oath of a pledge to inflict on herself, her husband can confirm it or her husband can nullify it. 
\v 14 But if her husband is completely silent from day to day, then he confirms all her vows or all her pledges that \add are\add* on her; he confirms them because he was silent to her on the day he heard \add them\add*. 
\v 15 But if he indeed nullifies them after he hears them, then he will bear her guilt.”
\p 
\v 16 These \add are\add* the decrees that Yahweh commanded Moses, as between a husband and his wife, and between a father and his daughter, \add while\add* her childhood \add is in\add* her father’s house.
\c 31
\s1 War Against the Midianites
\m 
\v 1 Yahweh spoke to Moses, saying, 
\v 2 “Seek vengeance for the ⸤Israelites⸥\f + \fr 31:2 \ft Literally “sons/children of Israel” \f* on the Midianites; afterward you will be gathered to your people.” 
\v 3 Moses spoke to the people, saying, “Arm yourself from among your men for the battle, so that they will ⸤go⸥\f + \fr 31:3 \ft Literally “be” \f* against Midian to mete out the vengeance of Yahweh on Midian. 
\v 4 A thousand from each tribe of every tribe of Israel you will send to battle.” 
\v 5 So theywere assigned from the thousands of Israel, a thousand from each tribe, twelve thousand equipped for battle. 
\v 6 Moses sent them, a thousand from each tribe, to the battle, and Phinehas son of Eleazar the priest to the battle with them, and the vessels of the sanctuary and the trumpets of the blast \add were\add* in his hand. 
\v 7 And they fought against Midian just as Yahweh commanded Moses, and they killed every male. 
\v 8 They killed the kings of Midian in addition to the ones they had slain: Evi and Rekem and Zur and Hur and Reba, the five kings of Midian; they also killed Balaam son of Beor by the sword. 
\v 9 The ⸤Israelites⸥\f + \fr 31:9 \ft Literally “sons/children of Israel” \f* took captive the women of Midian and their children, and they plundered all their domestic animals and all their livestock and all their wealth. 
\v 10 They burned all their cities where they dwelled and all their camps with fire. 
\v 11 They took all the plunder and all the war-booty with the humans\f + \fr 31:11 \ft Hebrew “human” \f* and domestic animals.\f + \fr 31:11 \ft Hebrew “animal” \f* 
\v 12 They brought the captives, the war-booty, and the plunder to Moses, and to Eleazar the priest, and to the community of the ⸤Israelites⸥,\f + \fr 31:12 \ft Literally “sons/children of Israel” \f* to the camp to the desert-plateau of Moab, which \add was\add* on \add the\add* Jordan \add across\add* Jericho.
\p 
\v 13 And Moses and Eleazar the priest and all the leaders of the community went out to meet them outside the camp. 
\v 14 But Moses was angry toward the leaders of the troops, the commanders of the thousands and the commanders of the hundreds, who came from the battle of the war. 
\v 15 And Moses said to them, “You have kept alive every female? 
\v 16 Behold, these women ⸤caused⸥\f + \fr 31:16 \ft Literally “were to” \f* the ⸤Israelites⸥,\f + \fr 31:16 \ft Literally “sons/children of Israel” \f* by the word of Balaam, to be in apostasy against Yahweh in the matter of Peor, so that the plague was among the community of Yahweh. 
\v 17 Now kill every male among the little children, and kill every woman who has ⸤had sexual intercourse with a man⸥.\f + \fr 31:17 \ft Literally “who has known the bed of a male” \f* 
\v 18 But all the females who have not ⸤had sexual intercourse with a man⸥,\f + \fr 31:18 \ft Literally “who has known the bed of a male” \f* keep alive for yourselves. 
\v 19 And you, camp outside the camp seven days; all who killed a person and all who touched the slain purify yourselves on the third day and on the seventh day, you and your captives. 
\v 20 You will purify yourselves and every garment and every object of hide and all the work of goats’ hair, and every object of wood.”
\p 
\v 21 Then Eleazar the priest said to the men of the battle who came from the war, “This \add is\add* the decree of the law that Yahweh commanded Moses. 
\v 22 Only the gold and the silver, the bronze, the iron, the tin, and the lead—
\v 23 everything that will go through the fire—you will pass through the fire, and it will be clean, and only in waters of impurity will it be purified. Whatever does not go into the fire you will pass through the waters. 
\v 24 And you will wash your garments on the seventh day and be clean, and afterward you will come into the camp.”
\s1 Division of the War-Booty
\m 
\v 25 Yahweh said to Moses, saying, 
\v 26 “You and Eleazar the priest and the leaders of the ⸤families⸥\f + \fr 31:26 \ft Literally “fathers” \f* of the community, ⸤take count⸥\f + \fr 31:26 \ft Literally “lift up the head” \f* of the war-booty that was captured, both humans\f + \fr 31:26 \ft Hebrew “human” \f* and the domestic animals;\f + \fr 31:26 \ft Hebrew “animal” \f* 
\v 27 divide the war-booty between those who engaged in the war, who went out to the battle, and all the community. 
\v 28 Exact a tribute for Yahweh from the men of the war, those who went out to the battle, one from five hundred persons, and from the cattle and from the male donkeys and from the flock; 
\v 29 take from their half and give it to Eleazar the priest \add as\add* a contribution to Yahweh. 
\v 30 From half of the ⸤Israelites⸥,\f + \fr 31:30 \ft Literally “sons/children of Israel” \f* take one \add share\add* drawn by lot from the fifty from the humans,\f + \fr 31:30 \ft Hebrew “human” \f* from the cattle, from the male donkeys, from the flock, from all the domestic animals,\f + \fr 31:30 \ft Hebrew “animal” \f* and give them to the Levities who keep the responsibilities of the tabernacle of Yahweh.” 
\v 31 Moses and Eleazar the priest did just as Yahweh commanded Moses.
\p 
\v 32 Thus the war-booty that remained of the plunder that the people of the battle plundered was six hundred and seventy-five thousand flocks \add of sheep\add*, 
\v 33 seventy-two thousand cattle, 
\v 34 sixty-one thousand male donkeys, 
\v 35 and the life of humankind, from the women who did not ⸤have sexual intercourse with a man⸥,\f + \fr 31:35 \ft Literally “who has known the bed of a male” \f* all the persons\f + \fr 31:35 \ft Hebrew “person” \f* were thirty-two thousand.
\p 
\v 36 The half of the share that was going out to the battle: the number of the flock \add of sheep\add* was thee hundred and thirty-seven thousand five hundred; 
\v 37 the tribute to Yahweh from the flock was six hundred and seventy-five; 
\v 38 and the cattle were thirty-six thousand; and the tribute to Yahweh \add was\add* seventy-two. 
\v 39 Of the male donkeys there were thirty thousand five hundred, and the tribute to Yahweh was sixty-one; 
\v 40 the humans\f + \fr 31:40 \ft Hebrew “human” \f* were sixteen thousand, and the tribute to Yahweh \add was\add* thirty-two persons. 
\v 41 And Moses gave away the tribute of the contribution of Yahweh to Eleazar the priest, just as Yahweh commanded Moses.
\p 
\v 42 From the half of the ⸤Israelites⸥,\f + \fr 31:42 \ft Literally “sons/children of Israel” \f* which Moses divided from the men who were fighting, 
\v 43 the half that belonged to the community was three hundred and thirty-seven thousand five hundred from the flock, 
\v 44 and thirty-six thousand cattle, 
\v 45 and thirty thousand five hundred male donkeys, 
\v 46 and sixteen thousand humans.\f + \fr 31:46 \ft Hebrew “human” \f* 
\v 47 From the half that belonged to the ⸤Israelites⸥,\f + \fr 31:47 \ft Literally “sons/children of Israel” \f* Moses took one share drawn by lot out of every fifty humans\f + \fr 31:47 \ft Hebrew “human” \f* and domestic animals, and he gave them to the Levites, who keep the responsibility of the tabernacle of Yahweh, just as Yahweh commanded Moses.
\p 
\v 48 Then the leaders of the thousands of the army, the commanders of the thousands and the commanders of the hundreds, approached Moses, 
\v 49 and they said to Moses, “Your servants have ⸤taken count⸥\f + \fr 31:49 \ft Literally “lifted up the head” \f* of the men of war who \add were\add* ⸤in our charge⸥,\f + \fr 31:49 \ft Literally “in our hand” \f* and no man is missing from us. 
\v 50 So we brought the offering of Yahweh, what each man found, objects of gold, bangles,\f + \fr 31:50 \ft Hebrew “bangle” \f* bracelets,\f + \fr 31:50 \ft Hebrew “bracelet” \f* rings,\f + \fr 31:50 \ft Hebrew “ring” \f* earrings,\f + \fr 31:50 \ft Hebrew “earring” \f* and female ornaments,\f + \fr 31:50 \ft Hebrew “ornament” \f* to make atonement for ourselves ⸤before⸥\f + \fr 31:50 \ft Literally “in the presence of” \f* Yahweh.” 
\v 51 Moses and Eleazar the priest took the gold from them, all objects of work. 
\v 52 All the gold of the contribution that they raised up to Yahweh, from the commanders of the thousands and the commanders of the hundreds, was sixteen thousand seven hundred and fifty shekels. 
\v 53 The men of battle plundered each for himself. 
\v 54 So Moses and Eleazar the priest took the gold from the commanders of the thousands and hundreds, and they brought it to the tent of the assembly as a memorial for the ⸤Israelites⸥\f + \fr 31:54 \ft Literally “sons/children of Israel” \f* before Yahweh.
\c 32
\s1 Gad and Reuben Inherit Gilead
\m 
\v 1 The descendants\f + \fr 32:1 \ft Or “sons” \f* of Reuben and the descendants\f + \fr 32:1 \ft Or “sons” \f* of Gad had a very large number of livestock. And they saw the land of Jazer and the land of Gilead, and behold it \add was\add* a place for livestock. 
\v 2 The descendants\f + \fr 32:2 \ft Or “sons” \f* of Gad and the descendants\f + \fr 32:2 \ft Or “sons” \f* of Reuben came, and they said to Moses and to Eleazar the priest and to the leaders of the community, saying, 
\v 3 “Ataroth, Dibon, Jazer, Nimrah, Heshbon, Elealeh, Sebam, Nebo, and Beon, 
\v 4 the land that Yahweh struck before the community of Israel, \add is\add* a land of livestock, and your servants have livestock.” 
\v 5 They said, “If we have found favor in ⸤your sight⸥,\f + \fr 32:5 \ft Literally “your eyes” \f* let this land be given to your servants as property; do not lead us \add across\add* the Jordan.”
\p 
\v 6 But Moses said to the descendants\f + \fr 32:6 \ft Or “sons” \f* of Gad and to the descendants\f + \fr 32:6 \ft Or “sons” \f* of Reuben, “Will your brothers go to war while you yourselves live here? 
\v 7 Why are you discouraging the hearts of the ⸤Israelites⸥\f + \fr 32:7 \ft Literally “sons/children of Israel” \f* from crossing into the land that Yahweh gave to them? 
\v 8 This is what your fathers did when I sent them from Kadesh Barnea to see the land. 
\v 9 When they went up to the valley\f + \fr 32:9 \ft Or “the wadi” \f* of Eshcol and saw the land, they discouraged the heart of the ⸤Israelites⸥\f + \fr 32:9 \ft Literally “sons/children of Israel” \f* so that they did not come to the land that Yahweh gave to them. 
\v 10 So ⸤Yahweh’s anger burned⸥\f + \fr 32:10 \ft Literally “Yahweh’s nose became hot” \f* on that day, and he swore an oath, saying, 
\v 11 ‘The men who went up from Egypt, from ⸤those twenty years old⸥\f + \fr 32:11 \ft Literally “a son of twenty years” \f* and above, will not see the land that I swore with an oath to Abraham, Isaac, and Jacob because they have not wholly followed me, 
\v 12 except Caleb son of Jephunneh the Kenizzite and Joshua son of Nun, because they followed Yahweh wholly.’ 
\v 13 And ⸤Yahweh became angry⸥,\f + \fr 32:13 \ft Literally “Yahweh’s nose became hot” \f* and he made them wander in the desert forty years until the entire generation who did evil in the ⸤sight of Yahweh⸥\f + \fr 32:13 \ft Literally “eyes of Yahweh” \f* ⸤had died⸥.\f + \fr 32:13 \ft Literally “had completed” \f* 
\v 14 Behold, you stand in the place of your fathers, a brood of sinful men, to increase still more ⸤Yahweh’s fierce anger⸥\f + \fr 32:14 \ft Literally “the fierce anger of Yahweh’s nose” \f* against Israel. 
\v 15 If you turn from following him, he will again abandon them\f + \fr 32:15 \ft Hebrew “him” \f* in the wilderness, and you would have destroyed all these people.”
\p 
\v 16 They came near to him and said, “We will build sheep pens here for \add the\add* flock of our livestock and cities for our little children; 
\v 17 but we ourselves will become armed \add and\add* ready before the ⸤Israelites⸥\f + \fr 32:17 \ft Literally “sons/children of Israel” \f* until we have brought them to their place, and our little children will live in the fortified cities because of the inhabitants of the land. 
\v 18 We will not return to our houses until the ⸤Israelites⸥\f + \fr 32:18 \ft Literally “sons/children of Israel” \f* each obtain their\f + \fr 32:18 \ft Hebrew “his” \f* inheritance for themselves. 
\v 19 For we will not take possession with them from across the Jordan and beyond because our inheritance has come to us from across the Jordan to the east.”
\p 
\v 20 So Moses said to them, “If you do this thing, if you arm yourselves ⸤before⸥\f + \fr 32:20 \ft Literally “in the presence of” \f* Yahweh for the war, 
\v 21 and everyone of you armed cross the Jordan ⸤before⸥\f + \fr 32:21 \ft Literally “in the presence of” \f* Yahweh until he has driven out his enemies from before him, 
\v 22 and the land is subdued ⸤before⸥\f + \fr 32:22 \ft Literally “in the presence of” \f* Yahweh, then afterward you will return and be free of obligation from Yahweh and from Israel, and this land will be your property ⸤before⸥\f + \fr 32:22 \ft Literally “in the presence of” \f* Yahweh. 
\v 23 But if you do not do so, behold, you have sinned against Yahweh, and know that your sin will find you. 
\v 24 Build for yourselves cities for your little children and sheep pens for your flocks; what has gone out from your mouth you will do.”
\p 
\v 25 So the descendants\f + \fr 32:25 \ft Or “sons” \f* of Gad and the descendants\f + \fr 32:25 \ft Or “sons” \f* of Reuben said to Moses, saying, “Your servants will do just as my lord commands. 
\v 26 Our little children, our wives, our livestock, and all of our animals\f + \fr 32:26 \ft Hebrew “animal” \f* ⸤will remain⸥\f + \fr 32:26 \ft Literally “will be there” \f* in the cities of Gilead, 
\v 27 but your servants, everyone who is armed for battle, will cross over ⸤before⸥\f + \fr 32:27 \ft Literally “in the presence of” \f* Yahweh to the war, just as my lord says.”
\p 
\v 28 So Moses commanded them, Eleazar the priest, Joshua son of Nun, and the heads of the ⸤families⸥\f + \fr 32:28 \ft Literally “fathers” \f* of the tribes of the ⸤Israelites⸥.\f + \fr 32:28 \ft Literally “sons/children of Israel” \f* 
\v 29 Moses said to them, “If the descendants\f + \fr 32:29 \ft Or “sons” \f* of Gad and the descendants\f + \fr 32:29 \ft Or “sons” \f* of Reuben, everyone who is armed for the war, cross over the Jordan ⸤before⸥\f + \fr 32:29 \ft Literally “in the presence of” \f* Yahweh, and the land is subdued before you, you will give them the land of Gilead as property. 
\v 30 But if they will not cross over with you armed, they will acquire land in your midst in Canaan.” 
\v 31 The descendants\f + \fr 32:31 \ft Or “sons” \f* of Gad and the descendants of Reuben answered and said, “What Yahweh has commanded your servants, we will do. 
\v 32 We ourselves will cross over armed ⸤before⸥\f + \fr 32:32 \ft Literally “in the presence of” \f* Yahweh to the land of Canaan, and the property of our inheritance \add will remain\add* with us beyond the Jordan.”
\p 
\v 33 So Moses gave to them, to the descendants\f + \fr 32:33 \ft Or “sons” \f* of Gad and the descendants\f + \fr 32:33 \ft Or “sons” \f* of Reuben, and to half of the tribe of Joseph’s son Manasseh, the kingdom of Sihon the king of Amorites and the kingdom of Og the king of the Bashan, the land with its cities \add and their\add* territories, the cities of the surrounding land. 
\v 34 The descendants\f + \fr 32:34 \ft Or “sons” \f* of Gad rebuilt Dibon, Ataroth, and Aroer, 
\v 35 and Atroth Shophan, Jazer, and Jogbehah, 
\v 36 and Beth Nimrah and Beth Haran, the cities of Mibzar, and the sheep pens for flocks. 
\v 37 The descendants\f + \fr 32:37 \ft Or “sons” \f* of Reuben rebuilt Heshbon, Elealeh, and Kiriathaim, 
\v 38 and Nebo, Baal Meon (their names\f + \fr 32:38 \ft Hebrew “name” \f* \add were\add* changed), and Sibmah, and ⸤they renamed⸥\f + \fr 32:38 \ft Literally “they called to names the names” \f* the cities that they rebuilt. 
\v 39 The descendants\f + \fr 32:39 \ft Or “sons” \f* of Makir son of Manasseh went to Gilead, and they captured it and drove out the Amorites\f + \fr 32:39 \ft Hebrew “Amorite” \f* who \add were\add* in it. 
\v 40 So Moses gave Gilead to Makir son of Manasseh, and he lived in it. 
\v 41 And Jair son of Manasseh went and captured their unwalled villages, and he called them Havvoth Jair. 
\v 42 Nobah went and captured Kenath and its villages, and he called it Nobah after his \add own\add* name.
\c 33
\s1 The Travels Are Recounted
\m 
\v 1 These \add were\add* the journeys of the ⸤Israelites⸥,\f + \fr 33:1 \ft Literally “sons/children of Israel” \f* who went out from the land of Egypt according to their divisions, by the hand of Moses and Aaron. 
\v 2 Moses wrote down their movements according to their journeys on the command of Yahweh, and these \add are\add* their journeys according to their movements. 
\v 3 They set out from Rameses on the first month, on the fifteenth day of the first month; on the next day after the Passover the ⸤Israelites⸥\f + \fr 33:3 \ft Literally “sons/children of Israel” \f* went out ⸤boldly⸥\f + \fr 33:3 \ft Literally “with a hand that was raised” \f* ⸤in the sight⸥\f + \fr 33:3 \ft Literally “for the eyes” \f* of all the Egyptians 
\v 4 while the Egyptians \add were\add* burying all the firstborn among them whom Yahweh struck. Yahweh \add also\add* executed punishments among their gods.
\p 
\v 5 Then the ⸤Israelites⸥\f + \fr 33:5 \ft Literally “sons/children of Israel” \f* set out from Rameses, and they camped in Succoth. 
\v 6 They journeyed from Succoth and camped in Etham, which \add is\add* on the edge of the desert. 
\v 7 Then they set out from Etham and returned to Pi-Hahiroth, which faces Baal Zephon, and they camped before Migdol. 
\v 8 They set out from Pi-Hahiroth and went through the midst of the sea into the desert; and they went a journey of three days into the desert of Etham and camped at Marah. 
\v 9 They set out from Marah and came to Elim, and in Elim \add there were\add* twelve springs of water and seventy palm trees, and they camped there. 
\v 10 They set out from Elim, and they camped at the ⸤Red Sea⸥.\f + \fr 33:10 \ft Literally “sea of reed” \f* 
\v 11 They set out from the ⸤Red Sea⸥\f + \fr 33:11 \ft Literally “sea of reed” \f* and camped at the desert of Sin. 
\v 12 They set out from the desert of Sin and camped at Dophkah. 
\v 13 They set out from Dophkah and camped at Alush. 
\v 14 They set out from Alush and encamped at Rephidim; and it was there \add that\add* the people had no water to drink. 
\v 15 They set out from Rephidim and camped in the desert of Sinai. 
\v 16 The set out from the desert of Sinai and camped at Kibroth Hattaavah.
\p 
\v 17 They set out from Kibroth Hattaavah and camped at Hazeroth. 
\v 18 They set out from Hazeroth and camped at Rithmah. 
\v 19 They set out from Rithmah and camped at Rimmon Perez. 
\v 20 They set out from Rimmon Perez and camped at Libnah. 
\v 21 They set out from Libnah and camped at Rissah. 
\v 22 They set out from Rissah and camped at Kehelathah. 
\v 23 They set out from Kehelathah and camped at Mount Shapher. 
\v 24 They set out from Mount Shapher and camped at Haradah. 
\v 25 They set out from Haradah and camped at Makheloth. 
\v 26 They set out from Makheloth and camped at Tahath. 
\v 27 They set out from Tahath and camped at Terah. 
\v 28 They set out from Terah and camped at Mithcah. 
\v 29 They set out from Mithcah and camped at Hashmonah. 
\v 30 They set out from Hashmonah and camped at Moserah. 
\v 31 They set out from Moserah and camped at Bene-Jaakan. 
\v 32 They set out from Bene-Jaakan and camped at Hor Haggidgad. 
\v 33 They set out from Hor Haggidgad and camped at Jotbathah. 
\v 34 They set out from Jotbathah and camped at Abronah. 
\v 35 They set out from Abronah and camped at Ezion Geber. 
\v 36 They set out from Ezion Geber and camped in the desert of Zin, that \add is\add*, Kadesh. 
\v 37 They set out from Kadesh and camped at Mount Hor, at the edge of the land of Edom.
\p 
\v 38 Aaron the priest went up to Mount Hor at the ⸤command⸥\f + \fr 33:38 \ft Literally “mouth” \f* of Yahweh, and he died there in the fortieth year after the ⸤Israelites⸥\f + \fr 33:38 \ft Literally “sons/children of Israel” \f* had gone out from the land of Egypt, in the fifth month on the first \add day\add* of the month. 
\v 39 Aaron was one hundred and twenty-three years old when he died on Mount Hor.
\p 
\v 40 Now the Canaanite, the king of Arad, who \add was\add* living in the Negev\f + \fr 33:40 \ft An arid region south of the Judean hills \f* in the land of Canaan, heard of the coming of the ⸤Israelites⸥.\f + \fr 33:40 \ft Literally “sons/children of Israel” \f*
\p 
\v 41 Then they set out from Mount Hor and camped at Zalmonah. 
\v 42 They set out from Zalmonah and camped at Punon. 
\v 43 They set out from Punon and camped at Oboth. 
\v 44 They set out from Oboth and camped at Iye Abarim, the boundary of Moab. 
\v 45 They set out from Iyim and camped at Dibon Gad. 
\v 46 They set out from Dibon Gad and camped at Almon-Diblatayim. 
\v 47 They set out from Almon-Diblatayim and camped in the mountains of Abarim, before Nebo. 
\v 48 They set out from the mountains of Abarim and camped on the desert-plateau of Moab by the Jordan \add across\add* Jericho. 
\v 49 They camped by the Jordan, from Beth-Jeshimoth up to Abel Shittim, on the desert-plateau of Moab.
\p 
\v 50 Then Yahweh spoke to Moses on the desert-plateau of Moab by \add the\add* Jordan \add across\add* Jericho, saying, 
\v 51 “Speak to the ⸤Israelites⸥\f + \fr 33:51 \ft Literally “sons/children of Israel” \f* and say to them, ‘When you cross the Jordan into the land of Canaan, 
\v 52 you will drive out the inhabitants of the land from your presence, and you will destroy all their idols and all the images of their molten idols, and you will demolish all their high places; 
\v 53 you will dispossess the land and live in it because I have given the land to you to possess it. 
\v 54 You will distribute the land by lot according to your clans; to the larger group you will give a larger inheritance, and to the smaller group you will give less inheritance. However the lot falls for him, there the lot will be. You will distribute it according to the tribes of your ancestors.\f + \fr 33:54 \ft Or “fathers” \f* 
\v 55 But if you do not drive out the inhabitants of the land from your presence, then it will happen that whomever you let remain of them will be like irritants in your eyes and like thorns in your sides; they will be your enemies in the land in which you live. 
\v 56 And just as I planned to do \add to\add* them, I will do to you.’ ”
\c 34
\s1 The Land of Canaan Is Divided
\m 
\v 1 Then Yahweh spoke to Moses, saying, 
\v 2 “Command the ⸤Israelites⸥\f + \fr 34:2 \ft Literally “sons/children of Israel” \f* and say to them, ‘When you come into the land of Canaan, this \add is\add* the land that was allotted to you as an inheritance, the land of Canaan according to its boundaries. 
\v 3 Your southern edge will be from the desert of Zin toward the side of Edom, and your southern border will be from the end of the Salt Sea\f + \fr 34:3 \ft That is, the Dead Sea \f* to the east; 
\v 4 your boundary will turn from the south to the ascent of Akrabbim\f + \fr 34:4 \ft Or “Scorpions” \f* and will pass over to Zin, and its limits will be from the south of Kadesh Barnea; it will continue to Hazar Addar and pass over to Azmon. 
\v 5 The boundary will turn from Azmon to the valley of Egypt, and its limits will be to the sea.
\p 
\v 6 “ ‘Your western boundary will be the Great Sea;\f + \fr 34:6 \ft That is, the Mediterranean \f* this will be your western boundary. 
\v 7 Your northern border will be from the Great Sea;\f + \fr 34:7 \ft That is, the Mediterranean \f* you will make a boundary from the Great Sea\f + \fr 34:7 \ft That is, the Mediterranean \f* to Mount Hor. 
\v 8 From Mount Hor you will make a boundary to reach Hamath; the limits of the territory will be at Zedad. 
\v 9 The boundary will go out to Ziphron, and its limits will be at Hazar Enan. This will be your boundary to the north.
\p 
\v 10 “ ‘You will mark out your eastern boundary from Hazar Enan to Shepham; 
\v 11 the boundary will go down from Shepham to Riblah from the east side of Ain, and the boundary will go down and border on the eastern side of the Sea of Kinnereth. 
\v 12 The boundary will go down to the Jordan, and its limits will be at the Salt Sea.\f + \fr 34:12 \ft That is, the Dead Sea \f* This will be your land according to its boundaries all around.’ ”
\p 
\v 13 So Moses commanded the ⸤Israelites⸥,\f + \fr 34:13 \ft Literally “sons/children of Israel” \f* saying, “This \add is\add* the land that you will obtain as an inheritance for yourself by lot, which Yahweh commanded to give to the nine and a half tribes. 
\v 14 For the tribe of the children of the Reubenites,\f + \fr 34:14 \ft Hebrew “Reubenite” \f* the children of the Gadites,\f + \fr 34:14 \ft Hebrew “Gadite” \f* and the half-tribe of Manasseh took their inheritance according to the house of their families.\f + \fr 34:14 \ft Or “their fathers” \f* 
\v 15 The two and a half tribes have taken their inheritance from beyond the Jordan \add across\add* Jericho, east toward the sunrise.”
\p 
\v 16 Yahweh spoke to Moses, saying, 
\v 17 “These \add are\add* the names of the men who divide up the land for your inheritance: Eleazar the priest and Joshua son of Nun. 
\v 18 You will take one leader from every tribe to divide up the land for inheritance. 
\v 19 These \add are\add* the names of the men: of the tribe of Judah, Caleb son of Jephunneh; 
\v 20 of the tribe of the descendants of Simeon, Samuel son of Ammihud; 
\v 21 of the tribe of Benjamin, Elidad son of Chislon; 
\v 22 of the tribe of the descendants\f + \fr 34:22 \ft Or “sons” \f* of Dan, the leader Bukki son of Jogli; 
\v 23 of the descendants\f + \fr 34:23 \ft Or “sons” \f* of Joseph, the tribe of the descendants\f + \fr 34:23 \ft Or “sons” \f* of Manasseh, the leader Hanniel son of Ephod. 
\v 24 Of the tribe of the descendants\f + \fr 34:24 \ft Or “sons” \f* of Ephraim, the leader Kemuel son of Shiphtan; 
\v 25 of the tribe of the descendants\f + \fr 34:25 \ft Or “sons” \f* of Zebulum, the leader Elizaphan son of Parnach; 
\v 26 of the tribe of the descendants\f + \fr 34:26 \ft Or “sons” \f* of Issachar, the leader Paltiel son of Azzan; 
\v 27 of the tribe of the descendants\f + \fr 34:27 \ft Or “sons” \f* of Asher, the leader Ahihud son of Shelomi; 
\v 28 of the tribe of the descendants\f + \fr 34:28 \ft Or “sons” \f* of Naphtali, the leader Pedahel son of Ammihud.” 
\v 29 These are those whom Yahweh commanded to allot to the ⸤Israelites⸥\f + \fr 34:29 \ft Literally “sons/children of Israel” \f* the land of Canaan.
\c 35
\s1 Cities for the Levites
\m 
\v 1 Yahweh spoke to Moses on the desert plains of Moab beyond the Jordan \add across\add* Jericho, saying, 
\v 2 “Command the ⸤Israelites⸥\f + \fr 35:2 \ft Literally “sons/children of Israel” \f* that they give to the Levites from the inheritance of their property cities to live in; and you will give to the Levites pastureland all around the cities.\f + \fr 35:2 \ft Hebrew “them” \f* 
\v 3 The cities will be theirs to live in, and their pasturelands will be for their domestic animals, for their possessions, and their animals.\f + \fr 35:3 \ft Hebrew “animal” \f*
\p 
\v 4 “The pasturelands of the cities that you will give to the Levites \add will extend\add* from the wall of the city to \add a distance of\add* a thousand cubits all around. 
\v 5 You will measure outside the city the eastern edge two thousand cubits, for the southern edge two thousand cubits, for the western edge two thousand cubits, and for the northern edge two thousand cubits, with the city in the middle; this will be for them the pasturelands of the cities.
\p 
\v 6 “All the cities that you will give the Levites will be six cities of refuge, to which the killer can flee; in addition to them you will give forty-two cities. 
\v 7 All the cities that you will give to the Levites will be forty-eight cities, them with their pasturelands. 
\v 8 And the cities that you will give from the property of the ⸤Israelites⸥,\f + \fr 35:8 \ft Literally “sons/children of Israel” \f* you will take more from the larger group and less from the smaller group; each of them will give according to the portion of their inheritance according to the portion that he inherits.”
\s1 Cities of Refuge
\m 
\v 9 Yahweh spoke to Moses, saying, 
\v 10 “Speak to the ⸤Israelites⸥\f + \fr 35:10 \ft Literally “sons/children of Israel” \f* and say to them, ‘When you cross the Jordan \add into\add* the land of Canaan, 
\v 11 you will select for yourselves cities for your cities of refuge, that a killer who has killed a person unintentionally can flee there. 
\v 12 The cities will be to you a refuge from a redeemer, so that the killer will not die until he stands before the community for judgment. 
\v 13 The cities that you are to give will be your six cities of refuge. 
\v 14 You will give three cities across the Jordan and three cities in the land of Canaan; they will be cities of refuge. 
\v 15 To the ⸤Israelites⸥,\f + \fr 35:15 \ft Literally “sons/children of Israel” \f* to the alien, and to the temporary resident in their midst there will be these six cities as a refuge to which anyone who unintentionally kills a person may flee.
\p 
\v 16 “ ‘But if he hit him with an object of iron, so that he dies, the killer must surely be put to death. 
\v 17 And if he hit him with a stone in the hand, by which he will die, and he does die, he \add is\add* a killer; the killer must surely be put to death. 
\v 18 Or if he hit him with a wooden object, by which he will die, and he does die, he \add is\add* a killer; the killer must surely be put to death. 
\v 19 The blood avenger himself will put the killer to death; he must put him to death when meeting him. 
\v 20 If he shoves him in hatred, or he throws something at him with intention, and he dies, 
\v 21 or if he hits him in hostility with his hand, and he dies, the one that struck him will put to death the killer when meeting him.
\p 
\v 22 “ ‘Or if in an instant he shoved him, not in hostility, or threw something at him without intention, 
\v 23 or with any stone, without seeing it dropped on him so that he dies, while \add he was\add* not seeking his injury, 
\v 24 then the community will judge between the striker and between the blood avenger according to these ordinances. 
\v 25 The community will deliver the killer from the hand of the blood avenger, and the community will restore him to the city of his refuge to which he fled; and he will live there in it until the death of the high priest who was anointed with holy oil. 
\v 26 But if the killer surely goes out of the territory of the city of his refuge to which he fled, 
\v 27 and the blood avenger finds him outside the territory of the city of his refuge, and the blood avenger kills the killer, ⸤he will not be guilty of blood⸥\f + \fr 35:27 \ft Literally “there will not be blood for him” \f* 
\v 28 because he must live in the city of his refuge until the death of the high priest. But after the death of the high priest the killer will return to the land of his property. 
\v 29 These things will be as a decree of justice for you for your generations in all your dwellings.
\p 
\v 30 “ ‘If anyone kills a person, the killer will be put to death ⸤according to the testimony⸥\f + \fr 35:30 \ft Literally “according to the mouth” \f* of witnesses, but someone cannot die on testimony of one person. 
\v 31 Also, you will not take a ransom payment for the life of a killer who \add is\add* guilty of death; indeed, he must surely be put to death. 
\v 32 You will not take a ransom payment for the one that flees to the city of his refuge, so that he may return to live in the land before the death of the priest. 
\v 33 So you will not pollute the land in which you are; because blood pollutes the land, and no atonement can be made for the land for the blood that is poured out on it except with the blood of the one who poured it out. 
\v 34 You will not defile the land on which you \add are\add* living because I \add am\add* living in the midst of it; I am Yahweh; I \add am\add* living in the midst of the ⸤Israelites⸥.’ ”\f + \fr 35:34 \ft Literally “sons/children of Israel” \f*
\c 36
\s1 Inheritance Through Marriage
\m 
\v 1 ⸤The leaders⸥\f + \fr 36:1 \ft Literally “The heads” \f* of the families\f + \fr 36:1 \ft Or “fathers” \f* of the clans of descendants\f + \fr 36:1 \ft Or “sons” \f* of Gilead the son of Makir, the son of Manasseh, of the clans of the descendants\f + \fr 36:1 \ft Or “sons” \f* of Joseph came near and spoke ⸤before⸥\f + \fr 36:1 \ft Literally “before the face of” \f* Moses and ⸤before⸥\f + \fr 36:1 \ft Literally “before the face of” \f* ⸤the leaders⸥\f + \fr 36:1 \ft Literally “the heads” \f* of the families\f + \fr 36:1 \ft Hebrew “of the fathers” \f* of the ⸤Israelites⸥.\f + \fr 36:1 \ft Literally “sons/children of Israel” \f* 
\v 2 And they said, “Yahweh commanded my lord to give the land by lot as an inheritance to the ⸤Israelites⸥,\f + \fr 36:2 \ft Literally “sons/children of Israel” \f* and my lord was commanded by Yahweh to give the inheritance of Zelophehad our brother to his daughters. 
\v 3 But if they become wives to one of the sons from \add another\add* tribe of the ⸤Israelites⸥,\f + \fr 36:3 \ft Literally “sons/children of Israel” \f* their inheritance will disappear from the inheritance of our ancestors,\f + \fr 36:3 \ft Or “fathers” \f* and it will be added to the inheritance of the tribe to which they belong; the lot of our inheritance would disappear. 
\v 4 When the Jubilee of the ⸤Israelites⸥\f + \fr 36:4 \ft Literally “sons/children of Israel” \f* ⸤comes⸥,\f + \fr 36:4 \ft Literally “will be” \f* it will be added to the inheritance of the tribe to which they belong; and their inheritance will disappear from the tribe of our father.”
\p 
\v 5 Then Moses commanded the ⸤Israelites⸥\f + \fr 36:5 \ft Literally “sons/children of Israel” \f* by the command of Yahweh, saying, “The tribe of the descendants\f + \fr 36:5 \ft Or “sons” \f* of Joseph \add is\add* right \add regarding what they are\add* speaking. 
\v 6 This \add is\add* the word that Yahweh commanded the daughters of Zelophehad, saying, ‘⸤Let them marry⸥\f + \fr 36:6 \ft Literally “Let them be as wives” \f* ⸤whomever they like⸥;\f + \fr 36:6 \ft Literally “they will be as the good in their eyes” \f* only ⸤they must marry⸥\f + \fr 36:6 \ft Literally “they must be as wives” \f* from within the clan of the tribe of their father. 
\v 7 Thus an inheritance of the ⸤Israelites⸥\f + \fr 36:7 \ft Literally “sons/children of Israel” \f* will not go around from tribe to tribe. Rather, the inheritance of each tribe of his father will remain with the ⸤Israelites⸥.\f + \fr 36:7 \ft Literally “sons/children of Israel” \f* 
\v 8 Every daughter who possesses an inheritance from the tribes of the ⸤Israelites⸥\f + \fr 36:8 \ft Literally “sons/children of Israel” \f* will ⸤marry⸥\f + \fr 36:8 \ft Literally “be a wife to” \f* one of the clan of the tribe of her father, so that the ⸤Israelites⸥\f + \fr 36:8 \ft Literally “sons/children of Israel” \f* will possess the inheritance of his ancestors.\f + \fr 36:8 \ft Or “fathers” \f* 
\v 9 Therefore an inheritance will not go around from \add one\add* tribe to another tribe because the tribes of the ⸤Israelites⸥\f + \fr 36:9 \ft Literally “sons/children of Israel” \f* will each hold to their \add own\add* inheritance.’ ”
\p 
\v 10 Just as Yahweh commanded to Moses, so the daughters of Zelophehad did: 
\v 11 Mahlah, Tirzah, Hoglah, Milcah, and Noah, the daughters of Zelophehad, ⸤married⸥\f + \fr 36:11 \ft Literally “were as wives to” \f* the sons of their uncles. 
\v 12 ⸤They married⸥\f + \fr 36:12 \ft Literally “They were as wives to” \f* those from the sons of Manasseh son of Joseph, and their inheritance ⸤remained⸥\f + \fr 36:12 \ft Literally “was” \f* among the tribe of the clan of their ancestors.\f + \fr 36:12 \ft Or “fathers” \f*
\p 
\v 13 These \add were\add* the commands and the stipulations that Yahweh commanded by the hand of Moses\f + \fr 36:13 \ft Or “through Moses” \f* to the ⸤Israelites⸥\f + \fr 36:13 \ft Literally “sons/children of Israel” \f* on the desert-plateaus of Moab by the Jordan \add across\add* Jericho.
